<TITLE> 5 killed in bus top accident in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 10 (bdnews24.com)  Five people, perched on bus top, were killed when they were hit by overhead iron structure of Kalurghat bridge on Thursday. Some 15 others were also injured in the accident that occurred when the Boalkhali-bound bus from Netrokona were passing through the bridge at 9:30am. The dead passengers have been identified as Sanu Mia, 35, Abdur Rashid, 35, Bachchu, 35, Insal Mia,35 and Anjuka, 70. Seven among the injured were identified as Zitu Mia, 45, Liton, 42, Siddique, 48, Saju Mia, 40, Nazrul, 46 and Nurul Islam, 45. The wounded passengers are now undergoing treatment at the Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Local journalist Mohammad Nazim told bdnews24.com that the passengers were going to visit Hawlapuri Darbar Sharif at Popadia village of Boalkhali upazilla in Chittagong. Boalkhali thana police officer Abdul Malek Mia told bdnews24.com three died on the spot and another, Bachchu, succumbed to injuries on way to hospital. Meanwhile, the accident caused a long queue of vehicles on both sides of Kalurghat bridg
